`crates/steno/src` is the entire `steno` compiler crate: source (`.steno`) → Plover JSON dictionaries + LSP snippets. External consumers (the three binaries in `bin/`, and transitively the Plover/nvim integrations) interact only through the re-exports in `lib.rs`; submodule paths are not part of the stable surface, and no file I/O happens anywhere in this tree — that's deliberately left to the binaries.

The pipeline is strictly linear and each stage's shared types are the coupling points a cross-cutting change must follow: `parse/` produces `Entry`/`Chunk`/`Expr` (the only place these variants are defined or produced); `expand/` consumes them through four ordered passes to produce `TypedEntry` (with `.terminal`/`.one_liner` flags that every downstream renderer must interpret consistently); `render/`, `blocks.rs`, and `snippet.rs` all consume `TypedEntry`/`Chunk` as three independent, non-interacting output targets — Plover keystrokes, `@literal` structural text, and LSP tabstop bodies respectively. `stroke/` is the only place a stroke is ever parsed, count-merged, or rendered to text (`parse_stroke`/`render_stroke`); `render/` calls into it but never reconstructs stroke text itself. `editor/` supplies the `Event`/`Behaviors` keystroke IR that both `render/` (via `PLAIN`/`SMART`/`SMART_INDENT`) and `blocks.rs` target — changing what `PLAIN`/`SMART` mean in `editor/` silently changes output in both consumers with no corresponding diff in their own code. `json_out.rs`'s `OrderedMap`/`to_json` is the sole serialization path used by `render/` and `snippet.rs` to keep dictionary output diffs stable and byte-parity with the ported TS tool; nothing else in the crate builds JSON. `error.rs` defines the one error per stage (`StenoError`, `ExpandError`, `RenderError`, `SnippetError`, `StrokeError`) that every fallible function in every subtree returns — nothing in the crate panics on malformed input, and `StrokeError → ExpandError` is the one deliberate error-structure-collapsing conversion.

Two invariants hold across the whole tree: all cursor/position arithmetic (`editor/`, `render/`) is in character offsets, never bytes; and `OrderedMap` insertion order, once established in `render/`/`snippet.rs`, is preserved unchanged all the way to `json_out::to_json`'s output — nothing re-sorts by key or by stroke. A typical multi-file change starts either in `parse/mod.rs` (new `Chunk` variant, forcing matching updates in `expand/`, `render/`, `blocks.rs`, `snippet.rs`) or in `stroke/keys.rs` (new key, forcing a check of `stroke/bank.rs`'s bit-weighting).

No `intent.md` is present for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.